<generalfeedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
<p>In the single regression model, two parameters are estimated: intercept and regression coefficiandt. For this reason, <span class="math inline">\(df = n-2\)</span>. In this case <span class="math inline">\(df = 30-2 = 28\)</span>. For a two-sided test with an alpha level of 0.01, a right-hand crossing probability of <span class="math inline">\(0.01 \div 2 = 0.005\)</span>. So you look up in the <em>t</em> table that value belonging to <span class="math inline">\(df = 28\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(t._{005}\)</span>, and dat is 2.763.</p>
</p>]]></text>
</generalfeedback>
